To most people in the fight game-in fact, even to the authoritative Ring Record Book and Boxing Encyclopedia  the welterweight champion of the World Boxing Association is known as Jose Pipino Cuevas. But, because someone once told him that "Pipino" made him sound like a clown, it is often dropped, in favor of simply "Jose Cuevas."

abstract: WASHINGTON, July 26 (AP)-- Jose-Luis Clerc and Brian Gottfried advanced to the final of the $175,000 Washington Star International tennis tournament today. Clerc, a 22-year-old Argentine, rallied to down Corrado Barazzutti of Italy, 2-6,6-3,6-3, and Gottfried defeated Gene Mayer, 6-3,6-2.
